id: pm-o1c53b
title: "Sentry PM-CLI-2D: storage-integrity history scan reads .jsonl directories as files"
description: "A production Sentry event from pm merge reconcile shows scanHistoryStreams throwing EISDIR when the history directory contains an entry named with a .jsonl suffix that is itself a directory. Harden the SDK storage-integrity primitive so hostile, malformed, or concurrently changing directory entries become structured integrity findings instead of crashing validation."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[6]: "area:history","area:sdk","area:validation",observability,sentry,storage-integrity
created_at: "2026-07-21T11:15:57.325Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T11:57:52.221Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T11:57:51.473Z"
author: codex-root
acceptance_criteria: A .jsonl-named directory cannot crash scanStorageIntegrity; the malformed entry is reported with a stable tracker-relative path and actionable detail; normal history streams remain unchanged; focused and full 100% coverage gates pass; the live Sentry issue is resolved only after exact-head proof.
parent: pm-o2kc
severity: high
environment: production
repro_steps: "Create a directory at .agents/pm/history/example.jsonl, then run pm validate --check-storage-integrity or pm merge reconcile."
resolution: "Converted unreadable history, settings, and schema candidates into deterministic storage-integrity findings with safe errno codes so validation primitives and merge reconciliation cannot crash on directory-shaped or raced entries."
expected_result: Storage-integrity validation completes deterministically and reports the non-regular history entry as an integrity finding without throwing.
actual_result: "History .jsonl, settings.json, and schema .json read failures now produce tracker-relative integrity rows with errno codes; scanned counts, full suite, and temporary-project SDK acceptance pass."
affected_version: 2026.7.20
fixed_version: next
component: sdk/governance/storage-integrity
regression: true
dependencies[3]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-7o0s,related,"2026-07-21T11:15:57.325Z",null,null
  pm-mfkv92,discovered_from,"2026-07-21T11:15:57.325Z",null,null
  pm-p5u6,related,"2026-07-21T11:15:57.325Z",null,null
comments[9]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T11:15:57.325Z",codex-root,"text=Duplicate check: searched all tracker statuses for PM-CLI-2D, EISDIR, scanHistoryStreams, illegal directory reads, and storage-integrity directory entries. No canonical item covers this exact failure; pm-mfkv92 is the merge-reconcile origin, pm-7o0s is prior disappearing-stream resilience, and pm-p5u6 owns release observability. Live evidence: Sentry PM-CLI-2D event 0705cf2439944c5f88ee0c2068c4add5 at 2026-07-21T07:29:28Z."
  "2026-07-21T11:16:35.285Z",codex-root,"Investigation: the merged main implementation still enumerates history and schema directories as bare names and unconditionally readFile()s any .jsonl/.json suffix. A directory or raced-away entry therefore escapes as EISDIR/ENOENT instead of producing a validation row. TDD scope covers both structurally identical scanner paths."
  "2026-07-21T11:24:32.968Z",codex-root,"TDD and acceptance evidence: the focused regression failed before implementation with EISDIR at scanHistoryStreams, then passed after unreadable history/schema candidates became structured findings. Full suite: 332 files, 6053 tests, exact 100% coverage (40694 statements, 28623 branches, 8264 functions, 39588 lines). ESLint, typecheck, jscpd zero clones, static/docstring/package/token-budget gates, and pm-changelog check all pass. A fresh temporary tracker with history/pm-directory.jsonl as a directory returned a storage_integrity error row and pm merge reconcile --dry-run completed without throwing."
  "2026-07-21T11:30:53.942Z",codex-root,"Greptile review 57c68db0-e734-477f-8608-b1af270c0fd5 blocked merge at 3/5: settings.json still propagates EISDIR, read failures lose the safe errno code, and history_streams_scanned semantics lack an explicit regression assertion. Reopened to address all three findings."
  "2026-07-21T11:37:42.688Z",codex-root,"Greptile remediation complete: settings.json EISDIR now becomes an unparseable_config_files row, history/schema read findings preserve the safe errno code without exposing absolute paths, and history_streams_scanned explicitly counts all nine candidate streams. Focused TDD, direct built-SDK malformed-settings acceptance, strict quality gates, and the full 332-file/6053-test suite pass at 100% (40700 statements, 28623 branches, 8265 functions, 39594 lines)."
  "2026-07-21T11:42:58.285Z",codex-root,Greptile re-review bdb92569-39d6-441f-af91-131367882baa rated the fix 5/5 and safe to merge with no review comments. Applying its sole non-blocking completeness note by asserting config_files_scanned alongside history_streams_scanned.
  "2026-07-21T11:43:57.877Z",codex-root,"Final completeness assertion passes: expanded malformed fixture counts nine history candidates and three configuration candidates while reporting every directory-shaped read failure. Focused suite and ESLint remain green; source implementation is unchanged from the exact 100% full-suite head reviewed 5/5 by Greptile."
  "2026-07-21T11:53:14.856Z",codex-root,"Hosted Gemini review identified one actionable medium finding: describeFileReadFailure casts unknown directly and could throw if a non-object value were thrown. Adding exhaustive error-shape guards and coverage before replying to and resolving thread PRRT_kwDORSgRDc6Sj54Y."
  "2026-07-21T11:57:50.690Z",codex-root,"Hosted Gemini remediation passes: describeFileReadFailure now safely narrows primitive, null, missing-code, non-string-code, and normal errno Error shapes; nonstandard throws produce error code UNKNOWN without crashing. Full suite now has 6054 tests and exact 100% coverage (40700 statements, 28629 branches, 8265 functions, 39594 lines); focused, ESLint, typecheck, and static quality gates pass."
files[2]{path,scope,note}:
